issue.title: Explore the Data
issue.body:
Let's explore the data and start with some basics plots (e.g. 1D, 2D histograms) of variables that might help us understand the planet data. 

**Action Items**
- [ ] Item 1: Plot some important planetary data parameters (orbital dynamics parameters for example)
- [ ] Item 2: Plot the positions of the host stars for each planetary system on a map of the Milky Way (in galactic coordinates to begin with)

In `planets_2019.11.01_20.07.23_variable_dict.npz` is a dictionary with the name of each column for each row in the table of planet data. Each variable also has a description. 

In `planets_2019.11.01_20.07.23_master_data.npz` is a list with each item in the list being a dictionary. The keys in these dictionaries are the names of the variables and the value for each key is the value of that variable for that exoplanet.
